PREAMBLE

The Government of the Republic of South Africa and the Government of the

Republic of France (hereinafter jointly referred to as the "Parties" and separately as a "Party");

CONSIDERING the friendly ties between the Republic of France and the Republic of South Africa;

WISHING to strengthen the friendly bilateral ties between their Armed Forces;

REAFFIRMING their

common commitment to the peaceful resolution of

international conflicts;

HEREBY AGREE as follows:

ARTICLE 1

AIM

The Parties shall co-operate in the field of defence.

ARTICLE 2

SCOPE AND GOALS

In accordance with their domestic law and subject to any restrictions of national security, the Parties shall co-operate in the field of defence co-operation by;

(a)

developing and formulating procedures for military co-operation between their respective Armed Forces;

